IVVO 11-Aug-18 07:17 AM
i just started on dota2 beginners guide, Scripting section. whats the difference between this KV package and lua package
Almouse 11-Aug-18 07:53 AM
@IVVO it's hard to know what you mean without knowing which guide you're referring to, but
KV and lua are two "languages" used for controlling how parts of the game work in your /scripts/ folder
game logic is done with lua, and items/abilities/units are described using KV (key-values)
however, you can also choose to define abilities/items with lua, and generally this is vastly preferred by most active modders
this is because lua is more powerful, and other reasons related to organisation/tidiness
somewhere on the web are sublime text packages for dota-lua and dota-kv (maybe that's what you meant by 'packages'?), honestly i don't think i'd recommend using either of them, for me they get in the way more often than they help

# is for arrays
arrays in lua are tables which you use in a right way
right way meaning you only use table.insert and table.remove to modify these tables
you can't count the number of entries in a random table with #

local counter = 0 for _, __ in pairs(table) do counter = counter + 1 end
